docs.abstract: A new report details how hackers in Iran have matured from defacing websites with crude photos to starting systematic cyberespionage campaigns. But they still feel they’re underpaid.
docs.snippet: A new report details how hackers in Iran have matured from defacing websites with crude photos to starting systematic cyberespionage campaigns. But they still feel they’re underpaid.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Between breaking into the email accounts of United States government officials, political dissidents and international human rights organizations, Iranian hackers liked to joke about their slow internet service, poor pay and lack of skilled colleagues.

headline.main: Iranian Hackers: Sophisticated, Frustrated and a Rising Global Threat
headline.print_headline: Inside Peek Shows Iranian Hackers’ Maturing Threat
